Title: Equivalence of Pixel-Driven and Rotation-Based Backprojectors for Tomographic Image Reconstruction  
Author: Jeffrey A. Fessler 
Address: Ann Arbor, MI 48109-2122  
Affiliation: 4240 EECS Bldg., University of Michigan,  
Note: REJECTED BY IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON MEDICAL IMAGING, SUBMITTED 1/31/1997 1  
Abstract: All methods for tomographic image reconstruction require a backprojection step. There have recently been several papers reporting empirical comparisons of various backprojection methods. This paper derives an analytical expression for "rotation-based" backprojectors, and shows analytically that pixel-driven back-projection is exactly equivalent to rotation-based backprojection when using the same interpolator. This equivalence holds for a very broad class of interpolation methods. 
